quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  21,1,"Mankind’s reckoning has drawn near, while they are in oblivion, disregarding<i class=""s"">(it) </i>."
  21,2,"No fresh reminder comes to them from their Lord but they listen to it playfully,"
  21,3,"their hearts distracted. And secretly did the unjust converse, “Is this anything but a human being like you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>? Will you go along with sorcery while you see?”"
  21,4,"<span class=""h"">He said<sup foot_note=""80567"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, “My Lord knows what is said in the heaven and the earth, for He is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing.”"
  21,5,"But they said, “A jumble of dreams; rather, he fabricated it; rather, he is a poet, so let him bring us a sign like those sent to the ancients.”"
  21,6,"None of the towns We annihilated before them had believed. Will they, then, believe?"
  21,7,"And never did We send before you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>but men to whom <span class=""h"">We reveal<sup foot_note=""80568"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, so ask the people of the Reminder if you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>do not know."
  21,8,"And never did We make them a mere body{1},<i class=""s"">(ones) </i>who eat<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>no food, for never were they immortal.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from plural to singular.
  21,9,"Then We fulfilled the promise to them, so We saved them together with whomever We will{1}, and We annihilated the extremists.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from past tense to present tense.
  21,10,"Most surely, We have sent down to you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>a Scripture containing your reminder. Do you not reason?"
